## What I Practiced (Hands-on)

- Building and running CORE scenarios (multi-router, multi-subnet)
- Generating attack traffic with **hping3**:
  - TCP SYN flood
  - UDP flood
  - ICMP flood
  - Source spoofing and reflection
- Capturing and validating traffic with **Wireshark**:
  - Targeted display filters (dst IP, dst port, SYN-only)
  - Quantifying traffic using **IO Graphs**
- Assessing application impact (curl-based HTTP client timing behavior)

